        "author": {
          "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
          "email": "alexey.zhuravlev@intel.com",
          "date": "2016-02-09 13:00:04.000000000",
          "tz": 180
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2016-04-11 02:51:59.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-7772 llog: do not destroy llog twice",
        "message": "LU-7772 llog: do not destroy llog twice\n\nif llog_process_thread() finds a llog corrupted, then it cancels\nall remaining records which in turn causes destroy of this llog.\nbut it's still referenced by the catalog's in-code structures\n(chd_head list) and llog_cat_close() at umount tries to destroy\nthis llog again. we can reset LLOG_F_ZAP_WHEN_EMPTY at destroy,\nso it never repeats.\n\nChange-Id: I8173d9dd2971fa5cce613e71555ca04e96b5512b\nSigned-off-by: Alex Zhuravlev <alexey.zhuravlev@intel.com>\nReviewed-on: http://review.whamcloud.com/18362\nTested-by: Jenkins\nTested-by: Maloo <hpdd-maloo@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: wangdi <di.wang@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Lai Siyao <lai.siyao@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Mike Pershin <mike.pershin@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <oleg.drokin@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
